                                            <condition key="intact"/>        
                                        </supportDesc>
                                    </objectDesc>
                                    <decoDesc>
                                        <decoNote xml:id="d6" type="miniature">
                                            <locus target="#6r"/>
                                            <desc>Tracing of the whole page from manuscript 'Miracles of Mary' (possibly from the 17th century) from the 
                                                'Cathedral Collection of MSS. Axum' (probably <placeName ref="INS0344AksumS"/>). Found by 
                                                <persName ref="PRS15033Playne"/> and painted while on the spot. The picture depicts the 
                                                <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin with the Child</ref>, surrounded by six 
                                                women and two men, one of whom carries a sword. The text following the picture contains the title of the seventh 
                                                miracle of Mary (possibly, according the counting of E. A. Budge: <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3593Miracle"/>)
                                                and mentions the owner, <persName ref="PRS15036ZamanfasQ"/>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">፯፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ 
                                                ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በክልኤ፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ። ጸሎታ፡ ወበረከታ፡ ወምሕረተ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ገብራ፡ ዘመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡
                                                ለዓለ<sic>ም</sic>፡ ዓለም።</foreign>. It is unclear, whether this text was copied as a caption to the painting on 
                                                <locus target="#6r"/> or was included in the description on back of the painting.</desc>
                                        </decoNote>
                                    </decoDesc>
                                </physDesc>
