                                    </objectDesc>
                                    <decoDesc>
                                        <decoNote xml:id="d9" type="miniature">
                                            <locus target="#9r"/>
                                            <desc>Picture by <persName ref="PRS15033Playne"/>, depicting the 
                                                <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion">Cruxifixion</ref> as well as 
                                                <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/>, indicated as: 'Copies (actual size) of scenes of "Crucifixion" and 
                                                "St George" from two separate series of folding pictures on parchment made to fold up, like a screen, between 
                                                wooden covers. Found by Beatrice Playne in <date when="1948">1948</date>
                                                in <placeName ref="LOC1881BetaGa">Bieta Gabriel, Lalibela</placeName>
                                                and in Aschette Mariam — Lasta — Ethiopia (17' Cent.), compare MS: Brit. Mus. No.'. 
                                                According to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/>
                                                <citedRange unit="page">159</citedRange></bibl>,
                                                'Aschette' is probably to be identified with <placeName ref="LOC2997Esatan">ʾAšatan Māryām</placeName>,
                                                the mentioned manuscript from the <placeName ref="INS00001BL">British Museum</placeName> is 
                                                probably <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient516"/>, while the subjects are to be identified as: 
                                                '<ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion</ref>;
                                                <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1047Apostles">6 Apostles</ref>; 
                                                <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1084JesusChrist">Christ in Zion</ref>; 
